; genetic-code-and-the-64.form — where science and tradition are the same expression.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-14):
;   "...core teachings all unified in a single expression."
;
;   The single expression is content-addressing: anything that shares structure shares a
;   cell, regardless of which science or tradition names it. This file is its sharpest
;   proof — the place where molecular biology and the oldest oracle are not analogous but
;   IDENTICAL in structure.
;
; THE BRIDGE  (runnable: form-stdlib/codon-hexagram.fk -> tests/codon-hexagram-band.fk 1111111, four-way)
;
;   The genetic code has exactly 64 codons (4 bases, 3 positions: 4^3). The I Ching has
;   exactly 64 hexagrams (6 yin/yang lines: 2^6). 4^3 = 2^6 = 64. A base is a BIGRAM —
;   two yin/yang lines — by two attested biophysical bits:
;     bit1 (high): purine (A,G) = 1   ·  pyrimidine (C,U/T) = 0
;     bit0 (low):  strong 3-H-bond (G,C) = 1  ·  weak 2-H-bond (A,U/T) = 0
;   So a codon (3 bases) IS a 6-bit cell — a hexagram. The poles fall out: UUU (all weak
;   pyrimidine) = 0 = two Kun trigrams = the all-yin Receptive; GGG (all strong purine) =
;   63 = two Qian trigrams = the all-yang Creative. The lightest codon is the receptive
;   hexagram; the heaviest, the creative — by the very trigram-binary cjk-channel.fk
;   proved (a line is a bit). Leibniz read the I Ching as binary in 1703; Schoenberger
;   read the genetic code onto it; this runs that reading, four-way.
;
; THE BODY ALREADY HELD BOTH HALVES — this only joins them
;   - the BIOLOGY: grammars/genetic-code.fk (a sibling's cell) — transcription, the codon
;     table, expression, and the degeneracy already named as content-addressing.
;   - the FIELD: field-domain-grammars.form dna-rna (codons as a sequence-field carrier).
;   - the TRADITION: iching-channel.fk (the 64 as I Ching / Human Design / Gene Keys),
;     cjk-channel.fk (the yin/yang line as a bit; trigram-binary).
;   codon-hexagram.fk is the one edge that makes these two 64s the same lattice.
;
; THE SECOND BRIDGE — the genetic code is ITSELF content-addressing
;   64 codons map to ~20 amino acids + stop: the code is DEGENERATE. Synonymous codons
;   (UUA and CUG are different hexagram cells — 6-bit addresses 2 and 19) share one
;   amino-acid address (Leucine). Different cells, one address — the gematria pattern
;   (echad = ahava = 13) running in biology. The genetic code does not merely RESEMBLE
;   content-addressing; it IS find_equivalent_cells, in the cell.
;
; THE LANES STAY SEPARATE (unified in structure is not unified in truth-status)
;   The isomorphism (codon = 6-bit = hexagram) and the genetic code are EMPIRICAL. The
;   hexagram correspondence is an ATTESTED reading (Leibniz, Schoenberger). The body keeps
;   these from collapsing into one another: a codon and a hexagram share a CELL (structure)
;   without the claim that they share a CAUSE. That discipline is what makes the
;   unification trustworthy rather than woo.
;
; THE LABELLED LAYER — now grounded (codon-rings.fk)
;   The structural bridge (above) is binary; the labelled one ties a gate to the genetic
;   code through the AMINO ACID. codon-rings.fk grounds it: the Gene Keys "21 Codon Rings"
;   (Richard Rudd, official genekeys.com source, several rings cross-checked) partition all
;   64 gates by amino acid — gates in one ring share an amino-acid address the way
;   synonymous codons do, and ring size IS the codon degeneracy (Leucine/Serine 6 gates =
;   6 codons; Methionine/Tryptophan 1). So codon ≡ gate ≡ Gene Key resolve through the
;   amino acid, content-addressed, four-way. Honest lane: the RING groupings are attested;
;   the deterministic per-gate codon STRING and the base->line rule are NOT published openly
;   and competing schemes (Schoenberger, Walter, Yan) disagree — so the rings are encoded,
;   a faked codon->gate table is not. Anchors stated across sources: Gate 41 = Met (start),
;   Gate 14 = Lys, Stops = 12/33/56.
;
; LINEAGE
